<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
Six new species were described (
<bibRefCitation author="Tautel, C" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="491 - 506" refId="B5537081" refString="Tautel, C, 2016. Nouvelles especes de geometres du Cambodge et des Philippines (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 121: 491 - 506" title="Nouvelles especes de geometres du Cambodge et des Philippines (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae)" volume="121" year="2016">Tautel 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
<bibRefCitation author="Han, H" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5535929" refString="Han, H, Xue, D, 2011. Fauna Sinica (Insecta Vol. 54. Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae). Science Press, Beijing" title="Fauna Sinica (Insecta Vol. 54. Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Geometrinae)." year="2011">Han and Xue (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
created the new combination 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chu" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Jodis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Jodis omeiensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omeiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Jodis omeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, stating that this species was transferred from the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Gelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gelasma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Gelasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warren, 1893; however, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Gelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gelasma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Gelasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been designated a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Maxates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maxates" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Maxates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Moore, [1887] by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, JD" journalOrPublisher="Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="147 - 326" refId="B5535998" refString="Holloway, JD, 1996. The moths of Borneo: Family Geometridae, subfamiles Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae and Geometrinae. Malayan Nature Journal 49: 147 - 326" title="The moths of Borneo: Family Geometridae, subfamiles Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae and Geometrinae" volume="49" year="1996">Holloway (1996)</bibRefCitation>
. Despite this synonymy, the combination 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Maxates" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maxates omeiensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omeiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Maxates omeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chu, 1981) does not appear to have ever been published between 1996 and 2011.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
<bibRefCitation author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev (2007)</bibRefCitation>
elevated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wehrli" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Jodis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Jodis putata subsp. orientalis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="putata" subSpecies="orientalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Jodis putata orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wehrli, 1923 from subspecies to species and subsequently synonymised it with 
<taxonomicName genus="J." lsidName="J. angulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">J. angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
